      </div>
      <div>
        <p>
          <em><span>Notice what these celebrations are </span></em><em
            ><u><span>for</span></u></em
          ><em
            ><span
              >. The Waffle Party rewards the employee who finished the work —
              and some work, finished, ends something. The Music Dance
              Experience is joy on a leash. And the &quot;Retirement Party&quot;
              sends off a coworker who will not remember leaving, because there
              will be no
            </span></em
          ><em><u><span>them</span></u></em><em
            ><span>
              left to remember. Each one is pleasant...sounding.</span
            ></em
          >
        </p>
        <p><em><strong><span>— C.C.</span></strong></em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <hr />
    <p>
      <span
        >That is the toolkit. The rest is yours — run it well. Remember that the
        employees in your care are people, even the ones who live only eight
        hours a day.</span
      >
    </p>
